trend_summary: Built-up footprint progressively expanded, especially in the north-west and along the main spine road, converting fields and scattered woodland into housing and small industrial lots. Road density rose and roundabouts appeared, while most southern forest stayed intact. Overall change shows steady suburbanisation from a mostly rural mosaic to a medium-density settlement.
notable_changes: Significant residential infill and new estates in the north-western quadrant.
New arterial and secondary roads, including additional junctions and roundabouts.
Several farmland blocks near the river converted to built structures and storage yards.
Patchwise clearing of central forest for mixed-use development.
Minor gain of tree cover in the far south through regrowth or conservation.
